  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/decision/cou1-accepted",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/org/fda-cdrh-osel",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Overall credibility assessment accepted despite single factor (Test conditions) below required level. The shortfall is mitigated by: (1) ASTM F1717 is a standardized single-condition protocol with no industry precedent for multi-condition testing; (2) all three QoIs meet the pre-specified E/uval < 1.96 acceptance criterion; (3) inter-laboratory reproducibility across two independent facilities provides additional confidence. A screening sensitivity analysis conducted during model development confirmed that the single-condition limitation does not introduce systematic bias into the QoI predictions. The 12 remaining factors all meet or exceed required levels. The model risk level 3 with medium assurance level is appropriate for a Class II device with medium decision consequence.",
